        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): fail fast on missing local probe auth",
        "body": "## Summary\n- fail fast for local loopback probe/status auth resolution when gateway auth is required but unresolved\n- return a local probe failure instead of attempting an anonymous loopback websocket connect\n- add focused regression coverage for the local authenticated probe/status paths\n\n## Testing\n- pnpm vitest run src/gateway/probe-auth.test.ts src/commands/gateway-status/helpers.test.ts src/commands/status.scan.shared.test.ts\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: When `gateway.auth.token` is a SecretRef that cannot resolve (env var missing/renamed, vault path broken), `openclaw` probe paths previously attempted a doomed WebSocket connect with empty auth before failing with a misleading \"connect failed\". This PR makes the probe short-circuit immediately with a specific \"SecretRef unresolved\" diagnostic.\n- **Real environment tested**: local `openclaw` build (current upstream/main + this PR) run against an isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME` whose `gateway.auth.token` is `{ source: \"env\", provider: \"default\", id: \"MISSING_GATEWAY_TOKEN_PROOF\" }`. The fail-fast vs proceed paths are toggled purely by whether that env var is set, isolating the changed code path.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  ```bash\n  # config: gateway.auth.token = SecretRef -> env:default:MISSING_GATEWAY_TOKEN_PROOF\n  # (A) env var ABSENT -> SecretRef unresolved:\n  env -u MISSING_GATEWAY_TOKEN_PROOF OPENCLAW_HOME=/tmp/probe-fail-home     node dist/index.js channels status --probe\n  # (B) env var SET -> SecretRef resolves:\n  MISSING_GATEWAY_TOKEN_PROOF=resolved-token-value OPENCLAW_HOME=/tmp/probe-fail-home     node dist/index.js channels status --probe\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix**: captured live from `node dist/index.js channels status --probe`:\n\n  (A) unresolved SecretRef — fail-fast short-circuit (the changed path):\n  ```\n  Checking channel status (probe)…\n  Gateway not reachable: gateway.auth.token is configured as a secret reference but is unavailable in this command path.\n  Fix: set OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN/OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD, pass explicit --token/--password,\n  or run a gateway command path that resolves secret references before credential selection.\n  ```\n\n  (B) same config, env var SET — SecretRef resolves, no short-circuit, proceeds to a real connect attempt:\n  ```\n  Checking channel status (probe)…\n  Gateway not reachable: gateway closed (1006 abnormal closure (no close frame)): no close reason\n  ```\n  The \"secret reference but is unavailable\" diagnostic appears ONLY in case (A). In (B) the probe gets past credential selection and actually attempts the WebSocket connect (1006 because no gateway is running at that temp home), proving the short-circuit is gated specifically on SecretRef resolution.\n- **Observed result after fix**: an unresolvable `gateway.auth.token` SecretRef produces an immediate, actionable diagnostic naming the exact config key and the remediation, with no doomed connect attempt. A resolvable SecretRef behaves exactly as before.\n- **What was not tested**: a real Vault-backed SecretRef provider fault (used the `env` provider with a missing var to deterministically reproduce the unresolved state). Live fault-injection on a production gateway (would require deliberately breaking auth on a host in use).\n",
        "branch": "fix/loopback-local-probe-auth",
        "head_sha": "b988d7c21ff045bfb7df810b9e0d1854f6935d08",
